definition.value: A member of the class of benzofurans that is a heterodimer of feruloylagmatine and para-coumarylagmatine where the former's hydroxy group has reacted across the latter's ethene double bond resulting in oxidative coupling to form a furan ring.
Zwitterionic form of gamma-amino-beta-hydroxybutyric acid having an anionic carboxy group and a protonated amino group.
Dianion of dTDP-L-dihydrostreptose arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups.
Dianion of UDP-alpha-D-xylose arising from deprotonation of both free diphosphate OH groups.
The conjugate base of (S)-3-(indol-3-yl)-2-oxobutyric acid.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the dianion of beta-D-fructofuranose 6-phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups.
Trianion of UDP-alpha-D-galacturonate arising from deprotonation of carboxy and diphosphate groups.
The dicarboxylate anion of 2-methylene-3-methylsuccinic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of GDP-6-deoxy-alpha-D-talose arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of 4-(L-alanin-3-yl)-2-hydroxy-cis,cis-muconate 6-semialdehyde having anionic carboxy groups and a protonated primary amine; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 1,6-dihydroxy-2-methylcyclohexa-2,4-dienecarboxylic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 2,4-dichloro-5-oxo-2,5-dihydro-2-furylacetic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A dianionic form of glycerone phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine compound formed by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of chlorogenic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
The carboxylate anion of N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1->4)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminosyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosylceramide.
The conjugate base of 3-(4-hydroxy-3,5-diiodophenyl)lactic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of dTDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.  It is an intermediate in dTDP-rhamnose biosynthesis.

An Aspidosperma alkaloid with formula C21H24N2O4 found in Catharantheus lanceus. Note that the stereoconfiguration of the epoxy group is based on CHEBI:144374, and of the 19 hydroxy group on CHEBI:144372 (the same enzyme produces the two).
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of 17alpha-(N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl)estradiol 3-glucosiduronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of 2-deoxy-D-ribose 5-phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major product at pH 7.3.
Anionic form of chondroitin D-glucuronate arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic acid groups of the repeating units; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 2-deoxy-D-gluconic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of undecaprenyl phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 3-dehydro-L-gulonic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 1-guanidino-1-deoxy-scyllo-inositol 4-phosphate having a dianionic phosphate group and a protonated guanidine; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of 11-O-demethyl-17-O-deacetylvindoline arising from protonation of the tertiary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained via global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4-bisphosphate.
Octaanion of myo-inositol 1,3,4,6-tetrakisphosphate arising from global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of O-succinyl-L-homoserine having anionic carboxy groups and a protonated amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of S-carboxymethyl-L-cysteine having anionic carboxy groups and a protonated amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Tricarboxylate anion of 2-caffeoylisocitric acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of 6-hydroxynicotinic acid; the major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the trianion of neryl diphosphate, arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianionic form of any N-acyl-D-mannosamine 6-phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of 2'-deoxyadenosine 5'-diphosphate (dADP); major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of D-ornithine having an anionic carboxy group and both amino groups protonated; major species at pH 7.3.
A carboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any N-acylglycine.
The conjugate acid of 1-amino-1-deoxy-scyllo-inositol arising from protonation of the primary amino group.
The conjugate acid of 7-O-acetylsalutaridinol arising from protonation of the tertiary amino function.
A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 2'-deoxyguanosine 5'-monophosphate (dGMP).
The dianion formed by deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups in any N-acylsphingosine 1-phosphate.
The conjugate base of questin arising from selective deprotonation of the 2-hydroxy group.
Dianion of sn-3-O-(geranylgeranyl)glycerol 1-phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups.
The conjugate base of 3-mercaptopyruvic acid.
Zwitterionic form of hypotaurocyamine having an anionic sulfinate group and a protonated guanidino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The (1E,4E,8E)-isomer of alpha-humulene.
Dicarboxylate anion of sinapoyltartronic acid.
